These model ordinances and recommendations must:
(a) Establish criteria for including tree bank programs in urban forestry ordinances;
(b) Establish criteria for designating areas for tree banks, including that tree banks must be located within areas identified as priority regions under RCW 76.15.100 and areas suffering from adverse environmental factors including, but not limited to, erosion, flooding, air or water pollution, and the urban heat island effect;
(c) Using the best available science, determine, at a minimum:
(i) The appropriate ratios of trees planted within the tree bank to trees removed elsewhere within the community; and
(ii) The appropriate species of trees to be used within the tree bank;
(d) Provide a tree selection and siting tool for use by local jurisdictions;
(e) Provide best practices for maintaining and growing newly planted trees within a tree bank, including by:
(i) Providing estimates of the cost to maintain and nurture newly planted trees to ensure their survival; and
(ii) Providing alternative methods for covering those costs, including through the imposition of an appropriate fee related to the use of the tree bank, to ensure that sufficient funds will be available to cover the costs of maintaining and nurturing the newly planted trees;
(f) Use the best available science to establish criteria for determining trees that, due to their size, environmental impact, or other significance are critical to retain during development;
(g) Prohibit a jurisdiction from requiring the retention outside of a critical area of any tree deemed by the jurisdiction to be significant, landmark, or otherwise of special import if such retention would affect a proposed development by:
(i) Reducing the maximum allowed density, number of allowed lots, or maximum allowed floor area ratio;
(ii) Precluding the construction of middle housing as defined in RCW 36.70A.030 or accessory dwelling units as defined in RCW 36.70A.696 ; or
(iii) Precluding the ability to establish any required access or utility connections to a lot; and
(h) Provide options for incentivizing developers to retain trees deemed by a jurisdiction to be significant, landmark, or otherwise of special import including, but not limited to, incentives related to:
(i) Increasing the allowed building density or height;
(ii) Reducing minimum required lot sizes;
(iii) Reducing or eliminating landscaping requirements; and
(iv) Reducing open space or setback requirements.

(11)(a) A dealer shall ensure that its business location designated in the license is monitored by a digital video surveillance system that meets all of the following requirements:
(i) The system shall clearly record images and, for systems located inside the premises, audio, of the area under surveillance;
(ii) Each camera shall be permanently mounted in a fixed location.

Cameras shall be placed in locations that allow the camera to clearly record activity occurring in all areas described in (a)(iii) of this subsection and reasonably produce recordings that allow for the clear identification of any person;
(iii) The areas recorded shall include, but are not limited to, all of the following:
(A) Interior views of all exterior doors, windows, and any other entries or exits to the premises;
(B) All areas where firearms are displayed; and
(C) All points of sale, sufficient to identify the parties involved in the transaction;
(iv) The system shall be capable of recording 24 hours per day at a frame rate no less than 15 frames per second, and must either (A) record continuously or (B) be activated by motion and remain active for at least 15 seconds after motion ceases to be detected;
(v) The media or device on which recordings are stored shall be secured in a manner to protect the recording from tampering, unauthorized access or use, or theft;
(vi) Recordings shall be maintained for a minimum of 90 days for all recordings of areas where firearms are displayed and points of sale, and for a minimum of 45 days for all recordings of interior views of exterior doors, windows, and any other entries or exits;
(vii) Recorded images shall clearly and accurately display the date and time;
