(1) In order to be eligible to participate in the Washington dream act service incentive grant program, a student must meet the following requirements:
(a) The student must be a resident student as defined in RCW 28B.96.010 ;
(b) The student has completed the Washington application for state financial aid;
(c) The student has indicated that they will attend an institution of higher education or is enrolled for at least six quarter credits or the equivalent semester credits and is making satisfactory progress in a program, as defined in rule by the office, at an institution of higher education;
